                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2865.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-21T17:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 21, 1912—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>With reference to your telegram of yesterday, 6 p.m., I am informed by the
                    manager of the American Smelting &amp; Refining Co. that all children and women
                    have left Asarco and Velardena. With regard to the conditions in those places I
                    have made urgent oral representations to the Mexican Government, but if the
                    Department considers it advisable that the American men should leave as well as
                    the women they will be so advised by me.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
